title: For Sale:  Colt Sporter Competition HBAR II with 4x20
postcontent: **A stipulation on this sale:  If you have a valid FL carry permit we can do the entire transaction at my home.  If you don't have a permit then option 2 is having a local dealer do a NICS check with appropriate forms.  Sorry to be a stickler, but this is my comfort zone given the state of the world I simply don't want to risk selling it to someone who can't pass a simple background check.  I'm happy to pay the NICS and FFL fees for the transaction at a local dealer so all it will cost you is a little time.  If you have a close local favorite dealer that's fine I have a local outfit I like as well.  I prefer a small mom and pop dealer in Brandon just great folks, but we can work that out if we get that far.  This Colt has spent all but ~ 300 rounds of it's life in the gun safe. This will be clear when you inspect the rifle in a variety of areas like the hammer, shell deflector and bolt carrier group.  The Colt was taken out of the safe a couple of times a year to ensure it was wet and put right back.  Even though the windage and elevation are set on mechanical zero I was able to take it to the range the week of July 4 and shoot 5 @ 100 to 8" offhand.  Obviously for optimal accuracy you will need to take the time to dial it in to a zero distance of your choice with appropriate elevation/windage changes.  Brought it home and gave it a thorough cleaning and it's ready to go to work for it's new owner.   *20" heavy barrel, 1 in 9 twist for .223/5.56.  For those not into the geekery of ballistics the twist rate might not mean much to you.  The slower the twist rate and longer the barrel the lighter the bullet for best accuracy.  Ideal for a 20" 1 in 9 is a 55g, but of course you can shoot whatever .223/5.56 cartridge you like.  Compare this to say a 16" barrel 1 in 7 which is better suited for a 62g/75g.  *Non-removable carry handle and the A2 buttstock even has the neat old school field kit compartment.  Colt factory A2 battle sights which were built around the Marine's 300 yard BZO protocol(8/3), but can be adjusted to accomodate any zero distance you like.*3 brand new Magpul 30 round magazines with dust covers(only 1 is pictured the others are in a storage case) and even an old Colt factory 8 round alloy mag.  The Colt mag is especially handy if you do any bench shooting off the older model Lead Sleds which don't allow for hi capacity mags to sit AR/M4 designs aligned.  *Uncle Mikes soft case with 5 external mag pouches, open pocket center slot and a forward velcro closed compartment.   Carry handle and shoulder strap.*Barska carry handle scope 4x20 with BDC out to 500 yards.  Brand new and obviously never sighted in.  This scope has a mount which allows you to maintain use of the irons even with the scope mounted which is quite ingenious.  Focus adjustment on eyepiece and BDC turret with additional windage and elevation turrets.  The box and materials have a mil-dot card, lens cap covers on bungee, lens cloth and sighting instructions.*2 different slings:  A brand new Condor Speedy 2 point with adjustable web and a standard 51" USGI carry sling with metal hardware(shown mounted on rifle pictures) so plenty of options to fulfill your offhand shooting nuances.  *Not pictured, but included is a spring loaded bipod that lightly clamps to the barrel which is nice if you need a make shift shooting rest on the go.  Fits perfectly in the front velcro pouch of the soft case.

title: For Sale:  Glock 19 FS Gen4 9mm - Free Shipping - No CC Fees
postcontent: BUY IT NOWThe Glock pistol, sometimes referred to by the manufacturer as Glock "Safe Action" Pistol, is a series of polymer-framed, short recoil operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistols designed and produced by Glock Ges.m.b.H., located in Deutsch-Wagram, Austria. Despite initial resistance from the market to accept a "plastic gun" due to durability and reliability concerns, and fears that the pistol would be "invisible" to metal detectors in airports, Glock pistols have become the company's most profitable line of products, commanding 65% of the market share of handguns for United States law enforcement agencies as well as supplying numerous national armed forces and security agencies worldwide. Glocks are also popular weapons amongst civilians for home/self defense and concealed/open carry.The company's founder, engineer Gaston Glock, had no experience with firearm design or manufacture at the time their first pistol, the Glock 17, was being prototyped. Glock did, however, have extensive experience in advanced synthetic polymers, knowledge of which was instrumental in the company's design of the first commercially successful line of pistols with a polymer frame. Glock introduced ferritic nitrocarburizing into the firearms industry as an anti-corrosion surface treatment for metal gun parts.The Glock 19 is effectively a reduced-size Glock 17, called the "Compact" by the manufacturer. It was first produced in 1988, primarily for military and law enforcement. The Glock 19 has a barrel and pistol grip that are shorter by approximately 12 mm (0.5 in) compared to the Glock 17 and uses a magazine with a standard capacity of 15 rounds. The pistol is compatible with factory magazines from the Glock 17 and Glock 18, with available capacities of 10, 17, 19, and 33 rounds. To preserve the operational reliability of the short recoil system, the mass of the slide remains the same as in the Glock 17 from which it is derived. With the exception of the slide, frame, barrel, locking block, recoil spring, guide rod, and slide lock spring, all of the other components are interchangeable between the models 17 and 19.Features:Length: 185 Mm / 7.28 In.Width: 30.00 Mm / 1.18 In.Length Between Sights: 153 Mm / 6.02 In.Height: 127 Mm / 4.99 In.Barrel Height: 32 Mm / 1.26 In.Barrel Length: 102 Mm / 4.01 In.Unloaded: 670 G / 23.65 Oz.Glock 19 FS 9mm Gen4Speed Loader All BlackLoaded: 855 G / 30.18 Oz.Trigger Pull: 2.5 Kg / 5.5 Lbs.Trigger Travel: 12.5 Mm / 0.49 In.Barrel Rifling: Right Hand, HexagonalLength Of Twist:2 50 Mm / 9.84 In.Standard: 15Optional: 17/33 includes three 15 Round Mags4 Backstraps Lock

title: For Sale:  BERETTA 92 FS
postcontent: This is the classic Beretta 92FS fairly used by me . The Beretta 92 pistol evolved from earlier Beretta designs, most notably the M1922 and M1951. From the M1922 comes the open slide design, while the alloy frame and locking block barrel were first used in the M1951. The grip angle and the front sight integrated with the slide were also common to earlier Beretta pistols. The Beretta 92 first appeared in 1975, the FS has an enlarged hammer pin that fits into a groove on the underside of the slide. Overall condition of this firearm, based on Blue Book of Gun Values guidelines, is 87%.
